<div id="review_817898380" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/817898380" />
    <a title="Fiona" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8641338-fiona"><img alt="Fiona" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611901771p2/8641338.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/817898380?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Fiona" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Fiona" href="/user/show/8641338-fiona">Fiona</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8641338-fiona?shelf=religion">religion</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer817898380" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4556006332754443061">A humorous but sincere attempt to study the Old and New Testaments and live by their rules for a year. AJ Jacobs, a non-practising Jew in New York, threw himself into this task. He read the Bible thoroughly, noted all its rules, and tried to put as many into practice as he reasonably could. He visited many different churches and consulted rabbis, pastors, professors of religion, worshippers and others, to gain more insight into people’s beliefs and their interpretations of the Bible. <br/><br/>There are a</span>
  <span id="freeText4556006332754443061" style="display:none">A humorous but sincere attempt to study the Old and New Testaments and live by their rules for a year. AJ Jacobs, a non-practising Jew in New York, threw himself into this task. He read the Bible thoroughly, noted all its rules, and tried to put as many into practice as he reasonably could. He visited many different churches and consulted rabbis, pastors, professors of religion, worshippers and others, to gain more insight into people’s beliefs and their interpretations of the Bible. <br /><br />There are a lot of serious issues discussed in this book. It’s not just light entertainment although it clearly is that too. It’s also very educational as he not only studies the interpretation of Biblical laws and guidance but also investigates their historical origins. So many rules were indicative of the social environment of the time and it often requires creative interpretation to apply them in the present day. Everyone cherry picks from the Bible. Almost without exception, for every rule or piece of guidance, there will be a contradiction to be found elsewhere. Whether you are a Fundamentalist Christian, Orthodox Jew, Lutheran or Catholic, agnostic or atheist, you can find passages in the Bible to support your world view.<br /><br />I’ve long had an interest in the Bible as a work of literature and as a historical document, in its origins and interpretation. I needed some lighter reading in the continuing lockdown and this ticked all my boxes. I found AJ honest, sincere, insightful, and lucky - to have the most understanding wife ever!<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4556006332754443061" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


